          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-1" n="1"><note place="foot">·Sh──────n <hi rend="italics">took this from Spectator</hi>, No. 603. Vol. 8.</note><hi rend="display-initial">M</hi>Y Time, O ye <hi rend="italics">Grattans</hi>, was happily spent,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-2" n="2">When <hi rend="italics">Bacchus</hi> went with me, wherever I went.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-3" n="3">For then I did nothing but sing, laugh and jest,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-4" n="4">Was ever a Toaper so merrily blest.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-5" n="5">But now I so cross and peevish am grown,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-6" n="6">Because I must go to my Wife back to Town.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-7" n="7">To the fondling and toying of <hi rend="italics">Honey</hi> and <hi rend="italics">Dear</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-8" n="8">And the Conjugal Comforts of horrid small Beer.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-9" n="9">My Daughter I ever was pleased to see,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-10" n="10">Come fawning and begging to sit on my Knee.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-11" n="11">My Wife too was pleased, and to the Child said,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-12" n="12">Come hold in your Belly, and hold up your Head.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-13" n="13">But now out of Humour, I, with a sour Look,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-14" n="14">Cry, <hi rend="italics">Huzzy</hi>, and give her a Souse with my Book.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-15" n="15">And I'll give her another── for why should she play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-16" n="16">Since my <hi rend="italics">Bacchus</hi>, and Glasses, and Friends are away.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-17" n="17">Wine! what of thy delicate Hue is become?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-18" n="18">That tinged our Glasses with Blew like a Plumb.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-19" n="19">Those Bottles, those Bumpers, why do they not smite,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-20" n="20">While we sit carowsing and drinking the White.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-21" n="21">Ah, Bumpers, I see, that our Wine is all done,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-22" n="22">Our Mirth falls of Course, when our Liquor is gone.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-23" n="23">Then since it is so, bring me here a supply,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M12835D--line-24" n="24">Begone froward Wife, for I'll drink till I dye.</l>
          </lg>
